<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<job id="recruitment-digest" xmlns="http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee" version="1.0">
    <!--
    Recruitment Digest Job (ATS expansion Phase 24)

    Purpose:
    Three periodic digests in one daily pass, each deciding for itself
    whether its period needs generating (event-derived idempotency):

    1. Weekly AI funnel narrative (recruitment.ai.digest.weekly-funnel
       .enabled): Danish prose over the P20 reporting projection's
       aggregates - numbers and enum codes only, never candidate data -
       appended as AI_DIGEST_GENERATED (narrative in payload so it
       survives anonymization) and posted to the recruitment channel by
       the SlackDigestRenderer reactor. One per ISO week.

    2. Quarterly AI rejection-pattern narrative (recruitment.ai.digest
       .rejection-patterns.enabled): same construction, one per ended
       FISCAL quarter (July-June year), generated within the first 14
       days of the new quarter - no retroactive backfill.

    3. DPO exception digest (recruitment.slack.dpo-digest.enabled +
       recruitment.gdpr.enabled): one weekly DM per DPO-role holder -
       Art. 14 notices due, consents expiring, open DSARs, upcoming
       auto-anonymizations and the partner-channel membership drift
       check. Every delivered DM appends DPO_DIGEST_SENT; the run only
       DMs recipients with no event for the week. An empty week still
       says "Nothing needs you this week".

    The daily cadence makes Monday delivery self-heal: a failed Monday
    (OpenAI or Slack outage) retries Tuesday on the same period key.
    One failing digest never stops the others.

    Schedule:
    Daily at 06:30 UTC via BatchScheduler - after the 05:45 GDPR sweep
    (the DPO digest reports post-sweep state), gated by
    dk.trustworks.recruitment.digest.enabled (default true).

    Similar to:
    recruitment-morning-brief.xml (the P23 clock-driven DM sweep)
    -->

    <listeners>
        <listener ref="jobMonitoringListener"/>
    </listeners>

    <step id="run-recruitment-digests">
        <listeners>
            <listener ref="stepProgressListener"/>
        </listeners>

        <batchlet ref="recruitmentDigestBatchlet"/>
    </step>
</job>
